body:
When added `setundef -zero` to generation of _syn0.v, autotest.sh give ERROR with the code below. Is it ok?

I changed this line in autotest.sh 
`test_passes -f "$frontend" -p "hierarchy; proc; opt; memory; opt; fsm; opt -full -fine" $fn`
to
`test_passes -f "$frontend" -p "hierarchy; proc; opt; memory; opt; fsm; setundef -zero; opt -full -fine; setundef -zero; opt -full -fine" $fn`

Then tried it with this code.

```
module cg (    
    C,
    GC,
    E
);

    input  C;
    output GC;
    input  E;

    reg ED;

always@(*) begin
    if(~C)
        ED = E;
end

    assign GC = C & ED;

endmodule
```

